<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Launching a Node.js Project with Vercel</title>
</head>
<body>

	<header>
		<h1>Launching a Node.js Project with Vercel</h1>
	</header>

	<section>
		<h2>Introduction</h2>
		<p>If you're building a Node.js application, you might want to deploy it to a hosting service to make it accessible to others. Vercel is a popular hosting service for Node.js applications that offers a simple and easy-to-use platform. In this guide, we'll walk through the steps to launch a Node.js project with Vercel.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Step 1: Create a Vercel Account</h2>
		<p>The first step is to create a Vercel account if you don't already have one. Go to the Vercel website and sign up for a free account. Once you've signed up, log in to the Vercel dashboard.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Step 2: Connect your Project to Vercel</h2>
		<p>Next, you need to connect your Node.js project to Vercel. You can do this by linking your GitHub or GitLab repository to Vercel. In the Vercel dashboard, click the "Import Project" button and select your repository. Vercel will automatically detect that it's a Node.js project and configure the settings for you.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Step 3: Configure your Project Settings</h2>
		<p>Once your project is connected, you can configure the settings for your deployment. This includes selecting the Node.js version, setting environment variables, and configuring build settings. You can also set up automatic deployments whenever you push new code to your repository.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Step 4: Deploy your Project</h2>
		<p>When you're ready to deploy your project, click the "Deploy" button in the Vercel dashboard. Vercel will build your project and deploy it to a URL that you can share with others. You can also set up custom domains, SSL certificates, and other advanced settings.</p>
	</section>

	<footer>
		<p>That's it! With Vercel, it's easy to launch a Node.js project and make it accessible to others.</p>
	</footer>

</body>
